# SLAM Services — Security-First .gitignore

# ==================== PERMANENT: Block Codespaces / Docker / Devcontainers ====================
# Local Windows ONLY. GitHub Codespaces + any .devcontainer/ definition were fully
# uninstalled (v2.44.16). These patterns ensure .devcontainer, .devcontainers,
# Dockerfiles, and compose files can NEVER be reintroduced or accidentally committed.
# Violating this (re-adding Codespaces/Docker support) requires explicit owner sign-off
# and a new Constitution amendment. Cursor/VS Code "Add Dev Container Config" will still
# create files locally, but they will be git-ignored and must be deleted immediately.
.devcontainer/
.devcontainers/
**/.devcontainer/
**/.devcontainers/
devcontainer.json
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.*
docker-compose*.yml
docker-compose*.yaml
.devcontainer.json
*.devcontainer*
# Also block common provisioning scripts that recreate remote envs
postCreateCommand.sh
onCreateCommand.sh
updateContentCommand.sh

# ==================== Client Data & Sensitive Files ====================
Data/
**/*.csv
**/*.xlsx
**/*.xls
feedback_log.csv
*.env
.secrets/
secrets/
*.pem
*.key
*.pfx
*.p12

# ==================== Secrets & Credentials ====================
# Never commit passwords, API keys, tokens, or config with secrets
SLAM_APP_PASSWORD
.secret
config.json
credentials*.*
*.log
deployment_diagnose.log
logextract/

# ==================== Generated / Large / Report Files ====================
# Large or auto-generated reports (do not commit to keep repo clean)
Project-Structure-Report.txt
*.report.txt
*structure-report*
*-report.txt
*.large.*
*.backup.*

# ==================== Development Artifacts ====================
Scripts/_streamlit_bank_uploads/
Scripts/cropped_checks_final_dynamic/
.venv.windows-backup*/
# Local Enhanced OCR (v2.44+) — cached EasyOCR/pipeline lines from real
# client bank statements. These accelerate the regression test
# (`Scripts/test_local_ocr_regression.py`) by avoiding a 10-min EasyOCR
# rerun each time, but they contain actual client transaction text and
# must never be committed. Regenerate locally via:
#   python Scripts/dump_easyocr_lines.py --dpi 200
#   python Scripts/dump_pipeline_ocr_lines.py
Scripts/_easyocr_cache_*.json
Scripts/_pipeline_lines.json
# v2.44.3: ad-hoc matcher diagnostic — runs the cropper + matcher and dumps
# every touched row to stdout. Useful for tuning `_is_clean_payee` and the
# Codespaces cropper DPI; not part of the regression suite. Local only.
Scripts/_diag_matcher.py
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python
env/
venv/
.venv/
ENV/
env.bak/
venv.bak/

# Build & Deploy
*.zip
*.tar.gz
dist/
build/
develop-eggs/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sdist/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
*.so
startup.sh.bak

# IDE & Tooling temp
.idea/
.vscode/.history/
.vscode/*.code-workspace
.cursor/*
!.cursor/rules/
!.cursor/rules/**
.kilo/
.kilocode/
.continue/
*.bak
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Node (future tooling)
node_modules/

# ==================== Allowed (explicitly not ignored) ====================
# .vscode/ workspace configs are intentionally committed (shared team settings)
!.vscode/
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/*.md

# Cursor rules (committed; rest of .cursor/ ignored above)
!.cursor/rules/
!.cursor/rules/**

# ==================== Retired / Audit Artifacts ====================
# Physical files from retired Kilo Code era + documentation coherence backups.
# These were intentionally removed from git tracking (v2.44.2) and must stay untracked.
Export-KiloCode-Output
.kilocode
docs-backups/

# ==================== G1 Spike artifacts (heavy output — never commit) ====================
# Tier-1 spike sources + docs are committed under Scripts/spike/ (see Scripts/spike/README.md).
# Heavy output (images, JSON diagnostics, large run artifacts) must never enter the repo.
Scripts/spike/artifacts/
Scripts/spike/**/artifacts/

# ==================== Working / Session Notes (temporary) ====================
# Decision briefs, sprint planning notes, and Cursor session transcripts.
# These will be reevaluated after the current G1 integration sprint.
# Do not commit unless explicitly promoted.
Documents/

# Dual-agent session state + captured deploy logs (local only)
.dual-agent-sessions/
deploy-logs-temp/

# ==================== One-off Review & Test Artifacts ====================
# Historical review outputs and ad-hoc test scripts with no ongoing purpose.
git-review-v2.37.txt
v2.37-final-review.txt
test_fast_vs_strict.py
Scripts/temp_*.py

# G1 spike: ephemeral session prompts (canonical narrative: repo-root Spike-Report + Scripts/spike/README.md)
Scripts/spike/CURSOR_PROMPT_*.md
Scripts/spike/Sprint_*_Prompt.md
*_review.txt
*review-v*.txt

# ==================== Historical Carryover Documents ====================
# "Business problem.docx" was a carryover from the original Power Apps initiation.
# It has no active purpose in the current Python/Streamlit project.
Business problem.docx
